  "url": "https://www.tamilmirror.lk/\u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd/\u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bc8-\u0ba8\u0bc0\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f-\u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc7-\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc8-\u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0ba9/175-302648",
  "time_ut": 1660936134,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bc8 \u0ba8\u0bc0\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc7 \u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0ba9",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "It was the de-banned organizations that made the allegations",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Today, it was the diaspora organizations whose ban was lifted that passed the motion in Geneva that the Sri Lankan Army was involved in war allegations.",
        "Former Chairperson of the Sri Lankan Human Rights Commission Professor Pradeepa Mahanamaheva said that the reason for lifting the ban on them is unknown.",
        "He said the above while addressing a meeting held yesterday (19) at the Government Information Department regarding media reporting on national security and law.",
        "During the Tsunami, the Triforce and the Police performed well. There was no talk in Geneva about the humanitarian action of the triads in this matter. Even during the corona infection, the soldiers performed well in the corona quarantine stations. Our country's media did not say anything about this. He said that while this is the case, people in Geneva will not have a chance to learn about the humanitarian activities of our country's soldiers.",
        "Today, six diaspora organizations have been banned in Sri Lanka. He said he did not know why the ban on the said organizations was lifted. A priest and I, a member of one of the said organizations, had a face-to-face discussion of the war accusations during the Geneva session.",
        "It was they who passed the resolution in Geneva that the Sri Lankan army was guilty of war. So now the government should use this opportunity to stop the propaganda being put forward by them against the army.",
        "It is people from these 6 organizations who are teaching students in classes that the military committed inhumane war crimes on May 19, 2009. He said that it was the members of these organizations who gave the list of names of soldiers to foreign countries to take legal action against them, saying that many people in the army were involved in war crimes."
      ],
